    <section id="intro">
      <span class="hero-tag">Lead Generation Guide · Updated June 2026</span>
      <h1>Sales Lead Generation: The Complete Guide to Finding and Converting Prospects</h1>

      <p><strong>Sales lead generation</strong> is the systematic process of identifying, attracting, and qualifying potential buyers — converting anonymous contacts into named prospects that a sales team can actively pursue through the pipeline.</p>

      <div class="verdict-box">
        <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Without a consistent flow of qualified prospects entering the sales process, no revenue pipeline exists. The data shows that 91% of marketers rank lead generation as their single most important marketing goal, and B2B lead generation services are projected to grow from $11.23 billion to $32.85 billion by 2035.</p>
      </div>

      <p>A "lead" is a person or organization that has shown identifiable interest in what you offer. This is distinct from general lead generation, which is broader and often marketing-owned. Sales lead generation focuses specifically on building an active pipeline — leads that a salesperson will contact, qualify, and attempt to convert into paying customers. It covers both inbound paths (a prospect finds your content and fills a form) and outbound paths (a sales rep identifies a target account and initiates the conversation).</p>

